snippet.textDisplay: Because you travel under a hectic schedule, think about taking Vitamin C supplements daily for you & the children. In addition Vitamin A for 10 days of the month is very good as a anti-viral precaution. Plus - go to a Chinese pharmacy & ask what is a good Chinese formula (in tiny pills) for as soon as a person has a cold. Nip it in the bud quickly and you recover quickly - it's always good to have on hands for your future trips. Enjoy the rest of your trip

snippet.textDisplay: "Hello, I saw your videos on the Chinese version of TikTok and I greatly admire and envy your ability to give up everything to travel the world. Firstly, coming to China, you have presented what you've observed and experienced in a very objective manner, and for that, I thank you. I lived abroad for about 10 years and have only recently returned to Shanghai. When I first went overseas, I often saw news and videos on YouTube that disparaged China. I went from feeling angry to adopting a more neutral stance over time. Due to differing policies, China really faces many challenges internationally, and as a Chinese person, I've also experienced unfair treatment. However, living a good life is what's important. China isn't perfect; with such a large population, there's significant variation in the quality of its citizens. But in this year since returning, I've clearly felt a shift among the youth. China is a country that started developing later than many developed nations and is still in a phase of development. It might take some time, and I hope that our friends from other countries can be more understanding. I believe we will continue to improve."

snippet.textDisplay: Have an excellent time in Hangzhou.  Drink more water, food there's a little on the salty side, but so good.  It's also the start of the other biggest historical landmark of China other than The Great Wall.  The Grand Canal links Hangzhou with Beijing (aka Jing-Hang waterway), which the first parts of it was built in the 300s BC, that's 2300years ago!
